    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.6112/16.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 450.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-01">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">October</hi> 1, 1912</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 434 of the 20th
                    ultimo and to previous correspondence in regard to the Ciénaga de Zapata
                    concession, I have the honor to transmit herewith enclosed (in compliance with
                    the request of Mr. Isaac K. Champion) copy<note n="1" xml:id="d449fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> of the opinion of his attorney as to the legality of the
                    Zapata concession and copies<note n="1" xml:id="d449fn2">Not printed.</note> and
                    translations of various communications addressed to the company and to the
                    President of the Republic by municipal governments and property owners who
                    express themselves as favoring the granting of the company’s concession.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S. Gibson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
